{
  "texts": [
    "The Iron emission blend covers almost the whole UV to optical range (Sect. 2.9.3).",
    "Guerras et al. (2013b) performed the only systematic study of microlensing of UV Fe II in a sizeable sample of 13 quasars.",
    "They focused on the range Åand identified strong microlensing in 4 systems.",
    "They derived a size of the corresponding emitting region of several light-days, comparable to the accretion disc size.",
    "Evidence for compact UV Fe II emission has also been reported in Q 2237+0305 (Sluse et al. 2011), H1413+117 (O'Dowd et al. 2015) (in [1590 -1680] Å) and in J1131-1231 (in [3080-3540] Å) by Sluse et al. (2007)."
  ]
}